<h1>@HI{{amari}}</h1>

<h2> Formation </h2>

<ol>
<li><strong>@HI{{amari}}</strong> <em>predicate</em>
</ol>

<h2> Definition </h2>

<p>
The adverb <strong>@HI{{amari}}</strong> expresses that the degree of the action of the verb is not great ("not much" or "not very").
</p>

<h2> Examples </h2>

<ol>
<li>
<table class="sentence" border=0>
  <tr class="jp"> <td>
      @HI{{@KJ{{private}}ha<strong>amari</strong>@KJ{{eat}}benai.}}
  </td> </tr>
  <tr class="en"> <td>
      I don't each very much.
  </td> </tr>
</table>
</ol>

<h2> Notes </h2>

<p>
<strong>@HI{{amari}}</strong> is usually found in negative sentences.
</p>

<p>
@HI{{anmari}} is a variant of <strong>@HI{{amari}}</strong> sometimes found in conversation.
</p>

